      <div class="annotation">
        <div class="ann-tag">Design Decision 14</div>
        <div class="ann-text">The persistent "Waiting for Sam's $50.00" banner names the specific participant and amount — not a generic spinner. This satisfies Norman's feedback principle: feedback should be specific and informative, not merely indicate that "something is happening."</div>
        <span class="ann-req">R2 — Real-time feedback</span>
      </div>
      <div class="annotation">
        <div class="ann-tag">Design Decision 15</div>
        <div class="ann-text">The large green checkmark and "Done" CTA give a clear, satisfying signal that the user's task is complete — even while the group transaction is still processing. This separates personal task completion from group transaction completion, reducing anxiety and social friction.</div>
        <span class="ann-req">R2 + R6</span>
      </div>
